The colour_names module
=======================

	>>> import colour_names
	>>> print colour_names.__doc__
	Methods to provide names for colours
	...


Basic colour names
-----------------

Start with the easy ones
	>>> show(colour_names.bw())
	['black', 'white']
	>>> show(colour_names.primaries())
	['red', 'green', 'blue']
	>>> show(colour_names.complementaries())
	['cyan', 'yellow', 'magenta']

All of those are considered basic
	>>> colour_names.basic() == colour_names.bw() + colour_names.primaries() + colour_names.complementaries()
	True

CGA colour names
----------------

CGA has all the basic names
	>>> all([name in colour_names.cga() for name in colour_names.basic()])
	True

And some extra ones
	>>> 'gray' in colour_names.cga() and 'gray' not in colour_names.basic()
	True

And light versions
	>>> 'light red' in colour_names.cga() and 'light cyan' in colour_names.cga()
	True
